    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.26a.92-93_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">9<del>3</del><add>2</add></fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        337 <hi rend="caps">E.</hi> 5th St.
                        rear house
                        New York <hi rend="caps">N.Y.</hi>
                        May 28 1958
                    </dateline>
                    
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>I received your address today from kindly Mr. Davidson of the Poetry Society of America whom I called. I am simply <hi rend="caps">OBSESSED</hi> with that supersplendescent poem of yours....<hi rend="caps">CONGRATULATIONS</hi>!!</p>
                
                <p>I wrote you some years ago &amp; still feel dismayed that you never replied. Did you recieve my letters?</p>
                
                <p>Tell me, please. <hi rend="caps">HOW</hi> you came to write that supersplendescent poem: "Let Me Live Out My Years"!!</p>
                
                <p>And what were the <hi rend="underline">original</hi> last two lines to it---
                    <lb/>
                    "Let me be as a tune swept fiddlestring
                    That feels the Master-Melody and snaps!"
                    <lb/>
                    -or- 
                    <lb/>
                    "O let me be a tune swept fiddlestring
                    That feels the Master-Melody--and snaps!"</p>
                
                <p>Personally, I prefer the latter. By the way, I know a man I feel sure you must've met yourself years ago: Robert Haven Schauffler author of- The Unknown Brahms, Beethoven The Man Who Freed Music The Poetry Cure, etc, etc, etc.</p>
                
                <p>I wonder whether you too imbibe the "Divine Art"?! I find it....absolutely...<hi rend="caps">SUPEREXCELLENT</hi>!!!!</p>
                
                <p>Pray let me hear from you if it is at all humanly possible.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Yours most sincerely,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Jerry Sims</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript>
                    <p><hi rend="caps">NB</hi> Ever meet Jack London or his friend George Sterling?!</p>
                </postscript>
                
            </div1>
            
            
